Chelsea manager, Thomas Tuchel, has delivered an update on the club’s ownership. The Blues are in the middle of a sale after Roman Abramovich was sanctioned by the UK government. According to Tuchel, there are four bidders left in the race and there will be more negotiations next week. He told a press conference on Friday: “It is also my info that it is down to four and there will be further negotiations in the next week.” Raine Group, a US-based investment bank, has whittled down all the interested parties in buying Chelsea Football Club to a shortlist of four. According to The Athletic, the shortlisted bids are from Todd Boehly, David Blitzer and Josh Harris, the Ricketts family and Boston Celtics owner Stephen Pagliuca.